This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on July 25, 2014, declaring July 27 as National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day. The proclamation honors the men and women who fought in the Korean War and recognizes their sacrifices in defending democracy. It also emphasizes the need for the nation to support and care for its veterans. The proclamation highlights the progress made by South Korea since the war and emphasizes the strong alliance between the United States and the Republic of Korea. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor Korean War veterans.